</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<emphasis box="[923,964,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gu.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[980,1128,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Dicrurobates</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Bush, S. E." box="[1144,1433,1377,1403]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="151 - 188" refId="ref25909" refString="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Bush, S. E. (2020) A new subgenus and eight new species of Guimaraesiella Eichler, 1949 (Phthiraptera: Ischnocera: Philopteridae: Brueelia - complex). Zootaxa, 4885 (2), 151 - 188. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4885.2.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2020</bibRefCitation>
. However, many species are either too poorly described to be placed in either of these subgenera, or represent groups that are so different from these four subgenera that they may warrant the erection of further subgenera within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1341,2015]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Among the taxa described here, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[563,888,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphagmotica" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[563,888,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella sphagmotica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[895,1033,1521,1547]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[895,1033,1521,1547]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1088,1436,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nouankaoensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1088,1436,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella nouankaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,1557,1583]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,291,1557,1583]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belong in the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[574,615,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gu.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1949" box="[634,808,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[634,808,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), based on the following characters: female subgenital plate without cross-piece (
<figureCitation box="[447,579,1593,1619]" captionStart="FIGURES 89–90" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,205,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@41.[295,1292,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 89–90. Female subgenital plates and vulval margins. 89, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 90, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825605/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs 89–90</figureCitation>
); gonopore terminal (
<figureCitation box="[820,951,1593,1619]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs 96, 99</figureCitation>
); mesosomal lobes not protruding (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 96, 99</figureCitation>
); distal thickening of mesosome interrupted medianly (
<figureCitation box="[806,938,1629,1656]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs 95, 98</figureCitation>
); dorsal preantennal suture not transversally continuous median to 
<emphasis box="[400,439,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">ads</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[454,585,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–88" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[173,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 87–88. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 87, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 88, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825603/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs 87–88</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Clayton, D. H. &amp; Bush, S. E." box="[604,886,1665,1691]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="451 - 497" refId="ref25972" refString="Gustafsson, D. R., Clayton, D. H. &amp; Bush, S. E. (2019 a) Twelve new species of Guimaraesiella (Phthiraptera: Ischnocera: Philopteridae) from &quot; babblers &quot; (Passeriformes: Leiothrichidae, Pellorneidae, Timaliidae) with a description of a new subgenus and a key to its species. Zootaxa, 4543 (4), 451 - 497. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4543.4.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Gustafsson 
<emphasis box="[736,785,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2019a)
</bibRefCitation>
also included the absence of 
<emphasis box="[1216,1255,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">aps</emphasis>
on the male abdominal segment IV as a character for 
<emphasis box="[589,630,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gu.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1949" box="[647,821,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[647,821,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but these setae are present in at least 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella flavala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Najer &amp; Sychra [in Najer 
<emphasis box="[529,577,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
.], 2012) and in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Coinde, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="Coinde" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[751,1263,1737,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menuraelyrae">
<emphasis box="[751,1087,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella menuraelyrae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Coinde, J. O." box="[1100,1255,1737,1764]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="418 - 427" refId="ref25513" refString="Coinde, J. O. (1859) Notes pour servir a l'histoire des epizoiques. Descriptions de quelques especes nouvelles appartenant aux genres: Docophorus, Nirmus, Lipeurus, etc. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 32, 418 - 427." type="journal article" year="1859">Coinde, 1859</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which also has three post-spiracular setae on tergopleurite IV in males; hence, absence of 
<emphasis box="[992,1031,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">aps</emphasis>
is not a good character for defining 
<emphasis box="[151,193,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gu.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1949" box="[209,383,1809,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[209,383,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1341,2015]" lastBlockId="36.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[260,584,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphagmotica">
<emphasis box="[260,584,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella sphagmotica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[639,853,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nouankaoensis">
<emphasis box="[639,853,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gu. nouankaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also part of the “core group” of 
<emphasis box="[1256,1297,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gu.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Malysheva, O. D. &amp; Tolstenkov, O. O. &amp; Bush, S. E." box="[394,681,1881,1907]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="846 - 857" refId="ref26058" refString="Gustafsson, D. R., Malysheva, O. D., Tolstenkov, O. O. &amp; Bush, S. E. (2019 b) Five new species of Guimaraesiella (Phthiraptera: Ischnocera) from broadbills (Aves: Passeriformes: Calyptomenidae, Eurylaimidae). Journal of Parasitology, 105, 846 - 857. https: // doi. org / 10.1645 / 19 - 88" type="journal article" year="2019">
Gustafsson 
<emphasis box="[526,575,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2019b)
</bibRefCitation>
, based primarily on following characters: mesosome without distal rugose nodi or area and ventral sclerite with a single anterior extension (
<figureCitation box="[961,1092,1917,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs 96, 99</figureCitation>
); dorsal preantennal suture not transversally continuous median to 
<emphasis box="[547,586,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">ads</emphasis>
and dorsal anterior plate thus continuous with roof of head posteriorly (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 87–88" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[173,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 87–88. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 87, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 88, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825603/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs 87–88</figureCitation>
). Most species in the “core group” have head shapes similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[960,1008,1989,2015]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Bush, S. E." box="[1151,1432,1989,2015]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 443" refId="ref25847" refString="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Bush, S. E. (2017) Morphological revision of the hyperdiverse Brueelia - complex (Insecta: Phthiraptera: Ischnocera: Philopteridae) with checklists and generic keys. Zootaxa, 4313 (1), 1 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4313.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Gustafsson &amp; Bush 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gustafsson, D. R. &amp; Malysheva, O. D. &amp; Tolstenkov, O. O. &amp; Bush, S. E." box="[151,417,151,177]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="846 - 857" refId="ref26058" refString="Gustafsson, D. R., Malysheva, O. D., Tolstenkov, O. O. &amp; Bush, S. E. (2019 b) Five new species of Guimaraesiella (Phthiraptera: Ischnocera) from broadbills (Aves: Passeriformes: Calyptomenidae, Eurylaimidae). Journal of Parasitology, 105, 846 - 857. https: // doi. org / 10.1645 / 19 - 88" type="journal article" year="2019">
Gustafsson 
<emphasis box="[282,330,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 2019b
</bibRefCitation>
), with the lateral margins of the preantennal head either clearly concave, or at most straight. The head shape of the two species of “core” 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eichler" authorityYear="1949" box="[642,816,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[642,816,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described here differ from most other described species in this “core” group, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[563,777,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nouankaoensis">
<emphasis box="[563,777,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Gu. nouankaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[832,1023,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphagmotica">
<emphasis box="[832,1023,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Gu. sphagmotica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be closely related.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
